					comprehensive presentation&nbsp;of&nbsp;measure&nbsp;theory,&nbsp;then&nbsp;to&nbsp;introduce&nbsp;the&nbsp;fundamental &nbsp;
					notions of&nbsp;modern probability&nbsp;theory, and ﬁnally&nbsp;to illustrate these&nbsp;concepts&nbsp;by &nbsp;
					the study of some&nbsp;important classes&nbsp;of&nbsp;stochastic processes. This text&nbsp;therefore &nbsp;
					consists of three&nbsp;parts&nbsp;of approximately&nbsp;the&nbsp;same&nbsp;size.&nbsp;In the&nbsp;ﬁrst part,&nbsp;we&nbsp;present &nbsp;
